Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1

(1 comment)

I'm -1 on this because:

1) (It looks to me) like the patch doesn't exactly match the commit message
2) There's no description in the bug or commit message describing why setting a custom location when an image is 'saving' is a problem.
3) It's not clearly spelled out why we have to make an API impacting change or if we've done due diligence to see if a non API impacting fix is possible.

Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1

Mike, could you please fix the commit message?

Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1

I'm echoing Stuart's comments. I'm OK with the change. But the commit message is not really matching the change. Multi locations is the most tricky corner of Glance. I'm thinking we should work out a user guide to make it clear. Back to this bug, based on my understanding, the purpose is only allowing adding locations for image which is in 'active' and 'queued' status, just only just handling the 'saving' and 'deactivated' status. Because 'active' means image has already in an immutable status, adding locations is fine. And 'queued' means there is no image data, so it's ok to add location to change it from 'queued' to 'active'. I'm happy to +2 if we can get a clear description of the problem. Thanks.
